# Nix Module Conventions

Read [bestpracticesnixos.md](../bestpracticesnixos.md) sections 5–8 before editing.

## Structure

```nix
{ config, lib, pkgs, pkgsUnstable, ... }:
let cfg = config.services.my-service; in
{
  options.services.my-service.enable = lib.mkEnableOption "my service";
  config = lib.mkIf cfg.enable { /* ... */ };
}
```

## Do / Don't

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| `lib.mkIf`, `lib.mkMerge` | `if` on config options; `//` with mkIf values |
| Declare `pkgsUnstable`, `inputs` in `{ ... }:` when used | Assume specialArgs silently |
| `openFirewall = false`; localhost bind for internal APIs | Auto-open firewall |
| One service → `modules/services/<name>.nix` | Bundle unrelated services |
| `config.age.secrets.*.path` at runtime | `builtins.readFile` secrets at eval |

## Paths

- New service: create `modules/services/<name>.nix`, add one import to `hosts/nixos/configuration.nix`.
- Secrets from services: `../../secrets/<name>.age`.
- Never bump `system.stateVersion` or `home.stateVersion` casually.
